Package fr.sorbonne_u.components.ports

Interface DataInboundPortI

  • All Superinterfaces:
    ComponentInterface, DataOfferedCI.PullCI, DataOfferedCI.PushCI, InboundPortI, OfferedCI, PortI, java.rmi.Remote, RequiredCI
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    AbstractDataInboundPort, PairDataInboundPort, PingPongDataInboundPort
    public interface DataInboundPortI
extends InboundPortI, DataOfferedCI.PullCI, DataOfferedCI.PushCI
    The interface DataInboundPortI represents the category of ports used by components exchanging data rather than being called for their services.

    Description

    A data inbound port is associated with a DataOfferedCI interface used to implement a basic interface to get data from a provider component. The primary way to get the data is the pull mode, where the client component calls the provider through the get() method which returns a piece of data. But the port can also be used in a push mode where the provider delivers the data to the client by calling a send method with a piece of data as parameter.

    Invariant

     invariant      getImplementedInterface() == getImplementedPullInterface()
 invariant      !connected() || isPublished()
 invariant      !connected() || getPortURI().equals(getClientPortURI())
 invariant      !connected() || (getServerPortURI() != null)
 invariant      !connected() == (getConnector() == null)
 invariant      !isRemotelyConnected() || connected()
 invariant      !isRemotelyConnected() || isDistributedlyPublished()
